element.name: Walkinstown Park Cache by Justy Dawson, Traditional Cache (2/2)
element.description: A very easy walk for all ages in an urban park in Walkinstown
element.long-description:
Cache number 3 of Justy Dawson. This is a small container hidden in a park that when I visited was completly deserted.
Its the last place you would suspect a park to be located. Easy to access and plenty of parking beside Lidl opposite.
The park has a revolving gate, so open at all hours.
The cache is a small amo box, contains a rolled up log book and geocoins/travel bugs
Please place back and hide where this is hidden. Watch for muggles.
